-- Saudis to Build New Industrial City for Women, Eqtisadiah Says
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-08-07T12:08:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/saudis-to-build-new-industrial-city-for-women-eqtisadiah-says.html
Saudi Arabia  will build an industrial
city in the Eastern city of Hafuf that will mainly employ women,
 al-Eqtisadiah  reported, citing Saleh al-Rasheed, acting director
general of the industrial cities authority.  The new city is under design and construction will be
tendered next year, al-Rasheed told the newspaper. The city is
expected to attract 500 million riyals ($133 million) in
investments and it will create 5,000 jobs for women in
industries such as textiles, pharmaceuticals and  food
processing .  To contact the reporter on this story:
